Market Definition

Alström Syndrome is an autosomal recessive, single gene disorder caused by mutations in ALMS1. It is multisystemic, with cone–rod retinal dystrophy which leads to juvenile blindness, obesity, sensorineural hearing loss, insulin resistance with hyperinsulinemia, and type 2 diabetes mellitus. Other clinical features includes hypertension, hypogonadism, urological abnormalities, hyperlipidemia, adult short stature, and bone-skeletal disturbance. This disease prevalence is rising and important diagnostic procedures and treatments will boost the growth of the market.



